  <description type="morphology">Stems 1–10 dm, densely to moderately hirsute proximally, moderately to sparsely so distally. Cauline leaves: blade conduplicate or flat distally, margins entire or denticulate, surfaces densely to sparsely hirsute. Racemes not secund; rachis straight. Fruiting pedicels 3–15 mm, sparsely pubescent or glabrous. Flowers: sepals reddish purple, dark maroon, or lilac-lavender, 5–13 mm, sparsely pubescent or glabrous; petals lavender to purple (with or without darker purple veins), 8–17 mm; adaxial filaments 8–13 mm. Fruits ascending to divaricate or reflexed, straight or arcuate; valves glabrous or sparsely pubescent. 2n = 28.</description>
