  <discussion>As delimited here, subsp. glandulosus is hetero-geneous, with varying flower color, fruit orientation, and indumentum density. It grows in Alameda, Colusa, Contra Costa, Lake, Mendocino, Monterey, Napa, San Benito, San Luis Obispo, Santa Barbara, Santa Clara, Solano, Sonoma, Stanislaus, and Tehama counties.</discussion>
